<div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />LDA makes $AD 0000, LDA [$00] makes $B200 (Says UNDEFINED and then BRK instructions), LDA ($00) makes $AD 0000,  LDA [$00],Y makes $B1 00, LDA ($00),Y makes $B9 0000. And for some reason, when the debugger for FCEUXD look at the LDA ($00),Y it says @ $0000,Y and says it's pointing to location $0000. &gt;.&lt;<br /></div><br />$B2 is the 65C02 (CMOS) opcode for LDA ($xx) (source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.oxyron.de/html/opcodesc02.html">http://www.oxyron.de/html/opcodesc02.html</a><!-- m -->)... so once again NESASM is just being silly. That opcode doesn't exist on the NES (NMOS) CPU.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Thu Dec 09, 2010 3:41 am</p><hr />
