<div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I am pretty sure. I've never checked the hex with LDA ($00) though so I am not sure it throws ZP into that or not.<br /></div><br />Wait a minute! Do you use [] or ()? If you are using parenthesis (which NESASM doesn't use for indirection, unlike all other 6502 assemblers), then it's probably generating absolute addressing instructions. For the program logic it makes no difference, so you can't tell unless you look at the binary. LDA $0000 works exactly the same as LDA $00, it just takes longer.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Dec 08, 2010 8:39 pm</p><hr />
